# ========================================================================================
# CodeChat - Complete Environment Configuration Reference
# ========================================================================================
# This is a master reference file showing ALL environment variables used in CodeChat.
# For actual configuration:
#   - Backend: Copy backend/.env.example to backend/.env
#   - Frontend: Copy frontend/.env.example to frontend/.env.local
# ========================================================================================

# ========================================================================================
# BACKEND ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (backend/.env)
# ========================================================================================

# --- NEO4J DATABASE (REQUIRED) ---
# Connection URI for Neo4j graph database
# For local: neo4j://127.0.0.1:7687
# For Neo4j Aura: neo4j+s://<instance-id>.databases.neo4j.io
NEO4J_URI=neo4j://127.0.0.1:7687

# Neo4j username (default: neo4j)
NEO4J_USERNAME=neo4j

# Neo4j password
NEO4J_PASSWORD=your_neo4j_password_here

# Neo4j database name (OPTIONAL, default: neo4j)
# NEO4J_DATABASE=neo4j

# --- GOOGLE GEMINI API (REQUIRED) ---
# API key for AI-powered summaries and query responses
# Get at: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# Gemini AI Model (OPTIONAL, default: gemini-2.0-flash-exp)
# Options: gemini-2.0-flash-exp, gemini-1.5-pro, gemini-1.5-flash, gemini-2.5-flash
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash-exp

# --- GITHUB (REQUIRED) ---
# Personal Access Token for repository access
# Create at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Required scopes: repo or public_repo
ACCESS_TOKEN=your_github_token_here

# --- CORS (OPTIONAL) ---
# Comma-separated list of allowed origins
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000

# ========================================================================================
# FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (frontend/.env.local)
# ========================================================================================

# --- API CONFIGURATION (OPTIONAL) ---
# Backend API URL (default: http://localhost:8000)
# Must be prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ for browser access
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# ========================================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE SUMMARY
# ========================================================================================
#
# REQUIRED (Backend):
#   ✓ NEO4J_URI            - Neo4j database connection URI
#   ✓ NEO4J_USERNAME       - Neo4j username
#   ✓ NEO4J_PASSWORD       - Neo4j password
#   ✓ GOOGLE_API_KEY       - Google Gemini API key
#   ✓ ACCESS_TOKEN         - GitHub Personal Access Token
#
# OPTIONAL (Backend):
#   ○ NEO4J_DATABASE       - Neo4j database name (default: neo4j)
#   ○ ALLOWED_ORIGINS      - CORS allowed origins (default: localhost:3000)
#   ○ GEMINI_MODEL         - Gemini AI model (default: gemini-2.0-flash-exp)
#
# OPTIONAL (Frontend):
#   ○ NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL  - Backend API URL (default: http://localhost:8000)
#
# ========================================================================================
# QUICK START GUIDE
# ========================================================================================
#
# 1. Backend Setup:
#    cd backend
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your actual credentials
#    python main.py
#
# 2. Frontend Setup:
#    cd frontend
#    cp .env.example .env.local  # (optional, uses defaults if not set)
#    npm install
#    npm run dev
#
# 3. Open http://localhost:3000
#
# ========================================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ========================================================================================
#
# - NEVER commit .env or .env.local files to version control
# - Keep your API keys and tokens secure
# - Use different credentials for development and production
# - Rotate tokens periodically
# - In production, use environment-specific configuration
# - GitHub token should have minimal required permissions
#
# ========================================================================================
